Paul,

Sounds like a bumper or bumper override hit. All it takes is a tap and then
it starts. We are fixing a similar spot on a current restoration. You can
see some pics on or site www.bustedbus.com click on the restoration link at
the bottom left corner. We will weld in a new piece from a parts bus. You
want to expose as much of the rust as possible but unless your going to weld
in more material you want to be careful not to cut out to much or any at
all. The por 15 stuff has great reviews.

